  "prompt": "Which US credit card charges no foreign transaction fees?",
  "response": "Several U.S. credit cards do not charge foreign transaction fees, making them ideal for international travel or purchases. Here are some popular options as of 2023:\n\n1. **Capital One Venture X Rewards Credit Card** - No foreign transaction fees and offers travel rewards.\n2. **Chase Sapphire Preferred\u00ae Card** - No foreign transaction fees and great for travel rewards.\n3. **Chase Sapphire Reserve\u00ae** - No foreign transaction fees with premium travel benefits.\n4. **Capital One Venture Rewards Credit Card** - No foreign transaction fees and earns travel rewards.\n5. **Bank of America\u00ae Travel Rewards Credit Card** - No foreign transaction fees and flexible travel rewards.\n6. **Discover it\u00ae Miles** - No foreign transaction fees, though Discover is less widely accepted internationally.\n7. **American Express\u00ae Gold Card** - No foreign transaction fees and offers dining and travel rewards (note: Amex acceptance varies globally).\n8. **Wells Fargo Autograph\u2120 Card** - No foreign transaction fees with strong rewards on travel, dining, and gas.\n9. **Citi Premier\u00ae Card** - No foreign transaction fees and offers points on travel, dining, and groceries.\n10. **PenFed Power Cash Rewards Visa Signature\u00ae Card** - No foreign transaction fees and offers cash back.\n\nAlways check the current terms and conditions of the card, as benefits and fees can change over time. Additionally, ensure the card is widely accepted in the countries you plan to visit (e.g., Visa and Mastercard are more universally accepted than American Express or Discover).",
